The paper discusses the performance of Deep Neural Networks in computer vision tasks, speech recognition, and machine translation, indicating that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper proposes a metric for evaluating the adversarial robustness of DNNs, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the mathematical explanation of the proposed metric, indicating that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses popular classification datasets, such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, and ImageNet, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
